text: This is a good hawker centre to go to for variety of cheap meals. The table seating is very open and always available. There is a wide variety of local and regional food. Cost is reasonable.

80 cents teh O gao. Not siap and hot. Maybe can stir less or ask for less sugar.

Great.

The old lady with the pink pony tail at the drinks stall is extremely rude. I had the misfortune to experience her ill temper when ordering kopi. It probably is the cheapest around here, but she had that "buay song", not happy to be here, DGAF energy. Ruined my day buying from her.
my mom and I love the horfun , most likely interest for me is Japanese food.  the noodles and dumplings they are tasty.

author_name: 陳 TAN明義 Meng Gee Gary
text: Decent price for Teh C Kosong Kar C at 1.20, should keep it that way...
